  • Method Details

    • canRestore

      boolean canRestore()
      This method will return true if this object can be restored at this time. There are two possible reason why this would be false. 1. the object was not archived in the first place; 2. The archive source is not currently available
      Returns:
      true if okay to restore

    • getArchiveDate

      Date getArchiveDate()
      Gets the value of the ArchiveDate field. When archiving was attempted on the root. Null if we never attempted to archive it.

    • getArchiveFailure

      ArchiveFailure getArchiveFailure()
      Gets the value of the ArchiveFailure field. Short version of the reason for a failure to archive

    • getArchiveFailureDetails

    • getArchiveSchemaInfo

    • getArchiveState

      ArchiveState getArchiveState()

    • getArchivedEntityPurgeDate

      Date getArchivedEntityPurgeDate()
      Gets the value of the ArchivedEntityPurgeDate field. Date when archived entity will be eligible for Purge

    • getExcludeReason

      String getExcludeReason()
      Gets the value of the ExcludeReason field. Reason for excluding or skipping the entity from archiving. If the ExcludeFromArchive bit is set, this gives the reason for excluding. Else, if this is not null, it is the reason for skipping.

    • getPublicIDOfRoot

      String getPublicIDOfRoot()
      Returns the publicID of the root entity.

      PublicID values are automatically created during the commit, if not previously set. The format is random, meeting security requirements based on current industry standards. For example:

      • pc:SYinDB2XTOgNZFs1NpxU8
      • pc:Sf8QS4N5RBS-h8_pj-Oy_
      • pc:SBwBzylneecSNr6_Ub4IO
      Your configuration code must not assume any particular format for PublicID values, in either the prefix or body portion of the string, or even assume the existence of a prefix. Do not make any assumptions at all about the content of a PublicID value, including expectations that values are sequential, numeric, or prefixed.

      Returns:
      The external id of the root.

    • isExcludedFromArchive

      Boolean isExcludedFromArchive()
      Gets the value of the ExcludedFromArchive field. Indicate if this entity should be excluded from archiving

    • isPendingReindex

      Boolean isPendingReindex()
      Gets the value of the PendingReindex field. Indicate that the archived entity is pending for re-indexing

    • reportArchiveProblem

      void reportArchiveProblem(String message)
      Report an issue that prevents this item from being archived. Usually called by a rule when it has determined that the item is not ready to be archived yet. Unlike skipFromArchiving(), this method does not return immediately and subsequent rules are processed.
      Parameters:
      message - The reason for skipping.

      Reset flag that marks the graph as excluded for archiving

    • setPublicIDOfRoot

      void setPublicIDOfRoot(String value)
      Sets the root public ID to the passed value.
      • Do not change the publicID once it is exposed externally.
      • The publicID must be unique.
      • The publicID must not leak information.
      If you do not set the publicID manually, then it is automatically set upon commit.
      Parameters:
      value - the value to be set as the publicID of the root entity.

    • skipFromArchiving

      void skipFromArchiving(String message)
      Skip archival of this item. Usually called by a rule when it has determined that the item is not ready to be archived yet. Unlike reportArchiveProblem(), this method returns immediately and no more rules are processed.
      Parameters:
      message - The reason for skipping.
